                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13150206" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 15 Nov 2011 02:47:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Part of 89-fb to trunk port.  Extremely trivial change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13150215" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 15 Nov 2011 03:14:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will revise patch.  The final strategy was to preallocate the core pools and then allow a timeout like in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3620&quot; title=&quot;Make HBCK Faster&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3620&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3620&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13156420" author="lhofhansl" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2011 00:05:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4805&quot; title=&quot;Allow better control of resource consumption in HTable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4805&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4805&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; allows control of the thread pool from the outside.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13156427" author="nspiegelberg" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2011 00:26:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3767&quot; title=&quot;Improve how HTable handles threads used for multi actions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3767&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3767&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ends up with a more elegant solution here to the coreThreads problem.  Still need to change the default name of the thread pool.  Going to apply the modified patch without review, since it&apos;s now just a debug wording change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13156431" author="nspiegelberg" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2011 00:40:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Lars : I think &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3767&quot; title=&quot;Improve how HTable handles threads used for multi actions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3767&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3767&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is the main fix that we need.  The benefit of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4805&quot; title=&quot;Allow better control of resource consumption in HTable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4805&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4805&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is the ability to have a global ThreadPool to share among all the HTable instances, correct?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13156449" author="lhofhansl" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2011 01:38:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Nicolas: Correct. It also add the ability to create &quot;unmanaged&quot; HConnections.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This allows for a philosophical change of managing HConnections rather than HTables. Together with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3767&quot; title=&quot;Improve how HTable handles threads used for multi actions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3767&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3767&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that obviates (for us at least) the need for HTablePool; HTable objects can be created whenever needed. I think that is a better way of looking at the client, especially in a AppServer setting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13156502" author="hudson" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2011 04:00:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in HBase-TRUNK #2476 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/HBase-TRUNK/2476/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/HBase-TRUNK/2476/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4787&quot; title=&quot;Make corePool as a configurable parameter in HTable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4787&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4787&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Rename HTable thread pool&lt;/p&gt;

